      <article id="tips">
        <h3>Currency Conversion Tips</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Compare the mid-market rate shown here against your bank's quoted rate before a transfer — the difference is the provider's margin.</li>
          <li>For large transfers, a specialist remittance service often beats a traditional bank on both rate and fee.</li>
          <li>Rates can move meaningfully within a single day; if timing isn't urgent, checking over a few days can reveal a better window.</li>
          <li>When traveling, card payments in local currency usually beat airport cash counters on rate.</li>
          <li>Always confirm whether a quoted rate includes fees, since a "no fee" transfer can still carry a wide spread.</li>
        </ul>
